> Our chefs are always brainstorming ways to make "chicken for dinner" a little more awesome. The delicious twist this week: a dynamic pan sauce with cherry jam, ancho chili powder, rich demi-glace, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Sweet and savory is the name of the game here, with the sides being no exception. Roasted carrots tossed with lemon zest and scallion-studded rice pair perfectly with the smoky-sweet chicken. Get ready for a flavor explosion.

== Roasted Carrots ==

Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} and season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until carrots are golden brown and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

== Scallion Rice ==

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @water{3/4%cup} and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}. Cover, reduce heat to low, and cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings: Melt 2 TBSP butter. Add 1 1/2 cups water.

== Cherry Ancho Chicken ==

While rice cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat same pan over medium heat. Add @butter{1%tablespoon}, remaining scallion whites, and @ancho chili powder{1%teaspoon} to taste (start with ¼ tsp and add more from there if you like things spicy). Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @chicken demi-glace{1}, @cherry jam{2%tablespoon}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a simmer; cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Squeeze in juice from 1 lemon wedge. Turn off heat.

> For 4 servings: Use 1/3 cup water.

== Assembly ==

Toss roasted carrots with lemon zest.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in half the scallion greens and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice, carrots, and chicken between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken. Sprinkle with remaining scallion greens. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.